From 53c8c2076a30314f0d2baf2104706500d99d4010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arunpandi Kannan <arunpand@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Nov 2025 16:08:44 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Remove STA if parsing
 peer_commit_element_ecc fails in SAE commit

When an AP sends an SAE confirm message, it starts a retransmit timer. In some cases,
the STA does not respond to the confirm message but instead sends an SAE commit
message again. This behavior can occur if the STA did not receive the SAE confirm
message from the AP and restarted the SAE session.

While parsing the SAE commit message, if the AP fails to parse peer_commit_element_ecc,
it currently responds to the STA with an unspecified failure status. However,
peer_commit_element_ecc remains set to NULL. Later, when the retransmit timer triggers
and attempts to send an SAE confirm message, the missing peer_commit_element_ecc
causes a crash.

To prevent this, remove the STA entry when parsing peer_commit_element_ecc
fails during SAE commit processing.

UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Remove STA if parsing peer_commit_element_ecc
failed in sae_commit parse

When AP sends sae confirm message, it starts retransmit timer. Sometimes STA
instead of responding to confirm message it sends sae commit message again.
This might be due to STA not receiving the sae_confirm message from AP and
restarts the sae session.

while parsing sae commit message, if AP fails to parse peer_commit_element_ecc,
it just sends response to STA with response unspecified failure. But
peer_commit_element_ecc is set to NULL. After sometime, retransmit timer kicks in
and tries to sae confirm message, since peer_commit_element_ecc is NULL due to
parse failure, it leads to crash.

Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency: None

Signed-off-by: Arunpandi Kannan <arunpand@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
index b347a37..f1ab9ff 100644
--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -1800,6 +1800,20 @@ static void handle_auth_sae(struct hostapd_data *hapd, struct sta_info *sta,
 			goto remove_sta;
 		}
 
+		if (resp == WLAN_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED_FAILURE &&
+		    sta->sae && sta->sae->tmp && ((sta->sae->tmp->ec &&
+		    sta->sae->tmp->peer_commit_element_ecc == NULL) ||
+		    (sta->sae->tmp->dh &&
+		    sta->sae->tmp->peer_commit_element_ffc == NULL))) {
+		      // Cancel timer, send response, cleanup
+		      sae_clear_retransmit_timer(hapd, sta);
+		      send_auth_reply(hapd, sta, sta->addr, WLAN_AUTH_SAE,
+				      auth_transaction, resp, NULL, 0, "auth-sae");
+		      sae_set_state(sta, SAE_NOTHING, "ECC/FFC peer commit parse failed");
+		      sae_clear_data(sta->sae);
+		      goto remove_sta;
+		}
+
 		if (resp == WLAN_STATUS_UNKNOWN_PASSWORD_IDENTIFIER) {
 			wpa_msg(hapd->msg_ctx, MSG_INFO,
 				WPA_EVENT_SAE_UNKNOWN_PASSWORD_IDENTIFIER
-- 
